{"lemma":"سُرِّيَّةٌ","slug":"سُرِّيَّةٌ","root":"س.ر.ر","root_slug":"س-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19433","n19657"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%91%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"concubine, chivese"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"company"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"secrecy, discretion"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of سِرِّيّ (sirriyy)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From سِرّ • (sirr) m."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19433","headword_ar":"سُرِّيَّةٌ","root":"sr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A concubine-slave; a female slave whom"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one takes as a possession and for concubitus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a female slave to whom one assigns a house, or chamber, in which he lodges her,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and whom he takes as a possession and for concubitus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEoliy~apN","text_ar":"فُعْلِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Mgh, Msb,) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sir~N","text_ar":"سِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying “ concubitus, ” (S, M, * Mgh, Msb, K,) or as signifying “ concealment, ” because a man often conceals and protects her from his wife; (S;) altered from the regular form of a rel. n., (S, M, Msb, K,) by its having damm [in the place of kesr]; (S, Msb;) for the rel. n. is sometimes thus altered, as in the instances of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duhoriY~N","text_ar":"دُهْرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahoru","text_ar":"الدَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suholiY~N","text_ar":"سُهْلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDu Als~aholapu","text_ar":"الاَرْضُ السَّهْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or it is with damm to distinguish it from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sir~iy~apN","text_ar":"سِرِّيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is applied to “ a free woman with whom one has sexual intercourse secretly, ” (Msb,) or “ one who prostitutes herself: ” (TA:) or it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sur~N","text_ar":"سُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suruwrN","text_ar":"سُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; because her owner rejoices in her; (Akh, * S, * Msb;) and if so, it is agreeable with analogy: (Msb:) so says A Heyth; and this is the best that has been said respecting it: (TA:) or it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuE~uwlapN","text_ar":"فُعُّولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarowN","text_ar":"سَرْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Mgh,) the latter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"being changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"for euphony, and then the [other]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"being incorporated into it and thus becoming"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"like it, after which the dammeh is changed into a kesreh because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is next to it: (M:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAriY~u","text_ar":"سَرَارِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraArK","text_ar":"سَرَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (ISk, TA;) the latter, by poetic license. (Ham p. 304.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","M","Mgh","Msb","ISk"]},{"entry_id":"n19657","headword_ar":"سُرِّيَّةٌ","root":"srw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", said by some to be originally of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuE~uwlapN","text_ar":"فُعُّولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarowN","text_ar":"سَرْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sr","text_ar":"سر"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}